{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Runs in the background and allows you to replicate a behavior from Cubase - when selecting items, the track selection is changed to match and the mixer view is scrolled to show the first selected track.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To exit, open the Actions menu, and click on: Running script: Lokasenna_Track selection follows item selection.lua down at the bottom.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Note: This script is a rewrite of: tritonality_X-Raym_Cubase_Style_SelectTrack_On_ItemSelect.lua\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It had a few bugs and I couldn't understand the original code well enough to fix them, so I opted to rewrite it from scratch.\par}
